diff:1377465927:1377465895:=157a158,178%0a> [[+++I make new rules+++]]%0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> %0a> [[#magic]]%0a> [++'''Magic:'''++]%0a> %0a> * Life spells cannot be used to cure extreme ailments like genetic conditions and cancer.  These are a major aspect of the person's pattern, and cannot be hand waved away with simple magic.  At best, one can model a spell after Regeneration that allows it to be suppressed for a month, before it wears off. This doesn't apply to diseases that are still purely viral or bacterial infections, like HIV, although the magic is vulgar for such major conditions.%0a> %0a> * Spirit magic - not just for the Shadow.  Any number of spells are can be used on any creature not native to the material world, including these: Exorcist's Eye, Exorcism, Otherworldly Instrument, Analyze Spirit, Read Spirit, Spiritual Bulwark, Bind Spirit, Spirit Possession, Materialize Spirit.  Generally, spells that would be useful for an Exorcist (ie. ending a threat) apply to any ephemeral critter.   Generally cannot be used to make friends and allies with them, though.%0a> %0a> * Glossamer Touch and Touch of the Grave, at Spirit 3 and Death 3, can enchant items to target Shadow spirits and ghosts, respectively.  %0a> %0a> * Converting mana to essence can be done with Spirit 2, Prime 1 instead of Spirit 4 Prime 4. Similarly, a [[ApprovedCreativeThaumaturgy#EPG|CT spell]] has been made allowing Death 2 Prime 1 to be used to convert mana to plasm, although this doesn't mean a mage inherently knows anything other than a ghost can use it. %0a> %0a> [[#thaumaturgy]]%0a> [++'''Creative Thaumaturgy'''++]%0a> %0a> Creative Thaumaturgy spells should be submitted first on the forums.  Following their approval by the GM staff, spells will be added to the [[ApprovedCreativeThaumaturgy | Creative Thaumaturgy Wiki]].%0a> %0a> [+++'''Alternate Rules in Effect'''+++]%0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a
