e noted that most restricted slots require justification.%0a%3c * A skill at four dots costs mages two restricted slots rather than one.%0a%3c * Gnosis 3 is one restricted slot, Gnosis 2 is not restricted.%0a%3c * The Mage Venue follows the General Restricted Slots found %0a%3c %25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Banned Merits List'''++]%0a%3c %25color=#1b9ad0%25[++'''Proximi Rules'''++]%0a%3c * You do not need to purchase the Sleepwalker or Proximi merit.  However, you must purchase the Unseen Sense (Supernal) merit.%0a%3c * Access to S.S. powers are a restricted slot, and requires extensive background justification.  Second Sight powers are NOT Supernal magic.   There needs to be a ''very'' strong reason why you have two kinds of magic.  You will also suffer prejudice.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cellnr:)%0a%3c [[#setting]]%0a%3c +++'''SETTING'''+++%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c This is the info on Mage Setting.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cell:)%0a%3c [[#magic]]%0a%3c [++'''Magic:'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c * Life spells cannot be used to cure extreme ailments like genetic conditions and cancer.  These are a major aspect of the person's pattern, and cannot be hand waved away with simple magic.  At best, one can model a spell after Regeneration that allows it to be suppressed for a month, before it wears off. This doesn't apply to diseases that are still purely viral or bacterial infections, like HIV, although the magic is vulgar for such major conditions.%0a%3c %0a%3c * Spirit magic - not just for the Shadow.  Any number of spells are can be used on any creature not native to the material world, including these: Exorcist's Eye, Exorcism, Otherworldly Instrument, Analyze Spirit, Read Spirit, Spiritual Bulwark, Bind Spirit, Spirit Possession, Materialize Spirit.  Generally, spells that would be useful for an Exorcist (ie. ending a threat) apply to any ephemeral critter.   Generally cannot be used to make friends and allies with them, though.%0a%3c %0a%3c * Glossamer Touch and Touch of the Grave, at Spirit 3 and Death 3, can enchant items to target Shadow spirits and ghosts, respectively.  %0a%3c %0a%3c * Converting mana to essence can be done with Spirit 2, Prime 1 instead of Spirit 4 Prime 4. Similarly, a [[ApprovedCreativeThaumaturgy#EPG|CT spell]] has been made allowing Death 2 Prime 1 to be used to convert mana to plasm, although this doesn't mean a mage inherently knows anything other than a ghost can use it. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Thaumaturgy]]%0a%3c [++'''Creative Thaumaturgy'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Creative Thaumaturgy spells should be submitted first on the forums.  Following their approval by the GM staff, spells will be added to the [[ApprovedCreativeThaumaturgy | Creative Thaumaturgy Wiki]].%0a%3c %0a%3c (:tableend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:include CityBook.MageNavigationBar:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
